		        &lt;br/&gt;CVE: CVE-2025-20164

A vulnerability in the lobby ambassador web interface of Cisco IOS XE Wireless Controller Software could allow an authenticated, remote attacker to remove arbitrary users that are defined on an affected device.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
This vulnerability is due to insufficient access control of actions executed by lobby ambassador users. An attacker could exploit this vulnerability by logging in to an affected device with a &lt;em&gt;lobby ambassador&lt;/em&gt; user account and sending crafted HTTP requests to the API. A successful exploit could allow the attacker to delete arbitrary user accounts on the device, including users with administrative privileges.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
